Here are 15 factual question-answer pairs based on the provided document page:

1. Q: What is the cost of a new personalausweis for people aged 24 and above?
A: EUR 37,00

2. Q: How much does it cost to apply for a personalausweis outside of one's hometown?
A: EUR 13,00 (Zuschlag)

3. Q: What is the cost of a vorläufiger Personalausweis (provisional ID)?
A: EUR 10,00

4. Q: Where can I find information on personalausweise on the hamburg.de website?
A: Click on "Formulare, Services & Links" and then select "Personalausweise"

5. Q: How do I apply for a personalausweis if it's been lost or stolen?
A: Apply at the Hamburg Service with proof of loss or theft

6. Q: What is the cost of applying for an electronic personalausweis (e-Pass)?
A: Not specified in the document

7. Q: Can I apply for a new personalausweis online?
A: No, according to the document, you need to apply in person at the Hamburg Service

8. Q: What is the cost of applying for an Aufenthaltstitel (residence permit)?
A: Not specified in the document

9. Q: Can I use the Speed Capture Terminal to take my biometric data?
A: Yes, but only if you need a personalausweis, Reisepass, Aufenthaltstitel, or Reiseausweis

10. Q: How much does it cost to use the Speed Capture Terminal?
A: 6,00 EUR (for a digital photo)

11. Q: Can I apply for a Fischereischein (fishing license) at the Hamburg Service?
A: No, according to the document, you need to bring your own biometric passphoto

12. Q: What is the cost of applying for an Führerschein (driver's license)?
A: Not specified in the document

13. Q: How do I apply for a new personalausweis if my name has changed?
A: Apply at the Hamburg Service with proof of name change

14. Q: Can I apply for a vorläufiger Personalausweis if my ID has been lost or stolen?
A: Yes, you can apply at the Hamburg Service with proof of loss or theft

15. Q: What is the opening hours of the Hamburg Service Curslack Einwohnerangelegenheiten?
A: Mo-Fr 9.30-12 Uhr